==English==
===Etymology===
From the past participle stem of Latin [[masticare]] ‘chew’, from Greek [[μαστιχαν]] ‘grind the teeth’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/'mæstɪkeɪt/}}
*{{audio|en-us-masticate.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|masticate|masticates|masticated|masticating}}
# ''(transitive)'' To [[chew]] (food).
#:''The cow stood, quietly '''masticating''' its [[cud]].''
# ''(transitive)'' To [[grind]] or [[knead]] something into a [[pulp]].

